Title: String bits and the Myers effect

Authors: Pedro J. Silva

Comments: 6 pages, talk given in the at the 24th annual

Montreal-Rochester-Syracuse-Toronto (MRST) Conference on Theoretical Physics,May 15-1702 2002. Proceedings will be published by the American Institute ofPhysicsJournal-ref: AIP Conf.Proc. 646 (2003) 77-82

Based on the non-abelian effective action for D1-branes, a new action formatrix string theory in non-trivial backgrounds is proposed. Once thebackground fields are included, new interactions bring the possibility ofnon-commutative solutions i.e. The Myers effect for ``string bits'' .